## Any other business

Mention was made of the fact that nothing had been heard from Jenkins since we
informed them they'd been accepted as an associated project. [They've since
been in touch and accepted.]

It was pointed out that the annual board election was coming up and the
spi-projects list had been emailed to reminded associated projects that they
might want to get involved.

The status of the Debian European trademark was asked about; our contact at the
SFLC had been on vacation but was expected back shortly.

Joshua mentioned that PgWest was at the end of September (in San Jose) and that
he thought it might be interesting to have some sort of SPI day as part of it.

Finally it was pointed out that we'd failed to produce an annual report for a
while and that we should try harder to achieve something this year.

